## Sheet: Reference

ANSWER FORMAT CODES
HHB	Him / Her / Both, with a short explanation. Best for division-of-labour questions (who cooks, who manages money).
SCALE	Agree–Disagree, 1–5. Best for intensity of a value or expectation.
MC	Multiple choice. Best for distinct positions on a topic.
OPEN	Open discussion prompt. No fixed answer — the point is to talk.
GUESS	Guess your partner's answer, then reveal. Newlywed-game style; great for fun and for gentle surprises.
RANK	Rank a set of options in order of priority. Great for gamified, compare-your-lists moments.
TIERS (depth)
1	Light — easy, low-stakes, good entry point into a category.
2	Medium — real substance, the everyday expectations couples skip.
3	Deep — the hard, vulnerable, or potentially divisive questions.
LEVELS (app staging — deeper/controversial come later, but all are selectable)
1	Warm-up — light, affirming, easy to answer.
2	Everyday — real but comfortable.
3	Deeper — weightier, more reflective.
4	Vulnerable — emotionally exposing.
5	Hot-button — the hard or potentially divisive ones.
STATUS
Draft	Captured but not yet reviewed.
Reviewed	Wording checked and tidied.
Approved	Ready to use in the app.
Needs work	Flagged — too thin, yes/no, duplicate, or unclear.
CATEGORY ID PREFIXES
